<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:90.74px" class="cls_018"><span class="cls_018">HAIR UNDER THE DOG’S PAWS</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:113.90px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">This is a big problem with dogs that have long hair. The hair continues</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:130.94px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">to grow between their toes. A lot of shabby hair comes down the nails</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:147.98px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">and under the paws making it very difficult to trim the nails.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:165.02px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">This hair can trap dirt, grass, mud and even snow in the winter</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:181.94px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">months. Also, the long hair on the paws can make it difficult to walk</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:198.98px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">on slippery surfaces and hardwood floors.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:222.02px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">It is important to trim this hair using hair clippers and trimmers to</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:239.09px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">make nail trimming easy and maintain paw hygiene.</span></div>
