<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:90.86px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">interacting with them on a day to day basis, that’s when the dog</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:107.90px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">starts picking up bad habits.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:147.86px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">In absence of exercise, they become restless and find ways to</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:164.90px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">entertain themselves.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:187.94px" class="cls_012"><span class="cls_012">Exercise can work wonders for your dog!</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:227.90px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">From reducing stress and anxiety to relieving  boredom, enough</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:244.97px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">exercise can be really beneficial for your dog. Proper amount of</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:262.01px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">exercise may also help your dog drop bad habits. Physical exercise</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.64px;top:279.05px" class="cls_010"><span class="cls_010">strengthens the body, while mental exercise strengthens the mind.</span></div>
